#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:40
msgid "File Security Scanner"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:41
msgid "Check if WordPress files have been tampered with"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:42
msgid "Compares your WordPress files against the originals to spot any suspicious changes. Helps detect if someone broke into your site and modified files, or if malicious code was added. Can automatically fix changed files by downloading fresh copies from WordPress.org, keeping backups just in case. Runs checks regularly and alerts you if anything looks wrong."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:43
msgid "Scan your WordPress files daily to make sure nobody has changed them without your permission. Catches hackers who try to sneak bad code into your site."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:47
msgid "Automatic Repair"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:48
msgid "Auto-repair modified core files"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:49
msgid "Automatically downloads and repairs modified WordPress core files when integrity violations are detected. Creates timestamped backups of existing files before replacement, downloads fresh copies from WordPress.org SVN repository, verifies checksums after repair, and maintains rollback capability for 7 days. Includes safety checks to prevent filesystem errors and detailed logging of all repair actions. Only repairs files in wp-admin and wp-includes directories - never touches wp-content, plugins, themes, or user uploads."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:50
msgid "Automatically repair any modified core files by downloading fresh copies from WordPress.org. Creates backups before making changes."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:54
msgid "Email Alerts"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:55
msgid "Send email when issues detected"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:56
msgid "Sends detailed email notifications to site administrators when core file integrity issues are detected. Emails include summary of modified files, list of unknown files found, timestamps of detection, severity levels, and direct links to the repair interface. Configurable alert frequency prevents email flooding while ensuring timely notification of critical security issues. Email templates are customizable and support HTML formatting for better readability."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:57
msgid "Get email notifications when modified or suspicious core files are detected so you can take immediate action."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:61
msgid "Exclude Non-Critical Files"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:62
msgid "Skip non-critical file checks"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:63
msgid "Excludes non-critical files from integrity scanning to reduce false positives and focus on security-sensitive files. Skips readme files, license.txt, sample configuration files, and other documentation that may be legitimately modified or removed. Maintains focus on PHP, JavaScript, and CSS files that could pose security risks if tampered with. Includes configurable exclusion patterns and ability to whitelist specific files or directories. Improves scan performance by reducing the number of files checked."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-core-integrity.php:64
msgid "Skip non-critical files like readme.txt and sample configurations to reduce false positive alerts and focus on security-critical files."
msgstr ""

