msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:40
msgid "Changes your WordPress admin area to use dark colors instead of bright white. Easier on your eyes, especially when working late at night or in dimly lit rooms. Can automatically match your computer's dark mode setting, or you can turn it on and off with a simple button. Great for reducing eye strain during long work sessions."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:41
msgid "Make WordPress admin pages use dark colors to be easier on your eyes. Perfect for working at night or if you find bright white screens uncomfortable."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:45
msgid "Match Computer Setting"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:46
msgid "Automatically use your computer's dark mode choice"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:47
msgid "WordPress will automatically switch between light and dark colors based on your computer's settings. If you have dark mode turned on in Windows, Mac, or Linux, WordPress will match it. Changes happen instantly when you update your computer's theme, no need to reload the page."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:48
msgid "Let WordPress automatically match whatever dark mode setting you have on your computer."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:52
msgid "Manual On/Off Switch"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-dark-mode.php:53
msgid "Add a button to turn dark mode on or off yourself"
