#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:30
msgid "Block External Font Loading"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:31
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:34
msgid "Block external font services to improve privacy and performance."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:32
msgid "Protect your visitors' privacy by blocking external font services including Google Fonts, Font Awesome, Adobe Fonts, and more. External fonts can track visitors across websites and slow down page load times. This feature intercepts and blocks font requests at multiple levels, removes font links from HTML output, and optionally replaces them with privacy-friendly system fonts. Granular controls let you whitelist specific fonts you want to keep while blocking others."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:33
msgid "External font services like Google Fonts track your visitors across the web and add unnecessary HTTP requests that slow down your site. Enable this to block tracking, improve page speed, and maintain full GDPR compliance while keeping your site looking great with system fonts."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:57
msgid "Block Google Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:58
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:61
msgid "Block fonts.googleapis.com and fonts.gstatic.com."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:59
msgid "Blocks all font requests to fonts.googleapis.com and fonts.gstatic.com, Google's most widely-used font delivery network. Google Fonts can track users across websites through font requests and unique identifiers. This prevents that tracking while removing unnecessary external dependencies that can slow down your site and create GDPR compliance issues."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:60
msgid "Google tracks every visitor who loads fonts from their CDN, building detailed profiles across millions of websites. Block this to protect your visitors' privacy and comply with GDPR regulations while improving page load speed."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:65
msgid "Block Font Awesome CDN"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:66
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:69
msgid "Block Font Awesome icon fonts from external CDN sources."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:67
msgid "Blocks Font Awesome icon fonts loaded from fontawesome.com, use.fontawesome.com, pro.fontawesome.com, kit.fontawesome.com, and the cloudflare CDN. Font Awesome is one of the most popular icon font libraries, but loading it from external CDNs creates privacy concerns and adds external dependencies. If you need Font Awesome icons, consider hosting the files locally instead."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:68
msgid "Font Awesome CDNs can track which icons are displayed on your site and collect visitor data. Most sites only use a handful of icons but load the entire library. Block external Font Awesome to eliminate tracking and improve performance."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:73
msgid "Block Adobe Fonts (Typekit)"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:74
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:77
msgid "Block Adobe Typekit and Edge Web Fonts services."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:75
msgid "Blocks fonts from use.typekit.net, use.typekit.com, use.edgefonts.net, and typekit.com. Adobe Fonts (formerly Typekit) is Adobe's premium web font service that can track visitors and collect analytics. Adobe Edge Web Fonts, while discontinued, is still used by older sites. Blocking these prevents Adobe from tracking your visitors across their extensive network."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:76
msgid "Adobe collects detailed analytics about font usage and visitor behavior across all sites using their font services. This data feeds into Adobe's broader tracking ecosystem. Block it to keep your visitors' data private and reduce external dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:81
msgid "Block Bunny Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:82
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:85
msgid "Block fonts.bunny.net privacy-focused font CDN."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:83
msgid "Blocks fonts from fonts.bunny.net, a privacy-focused alternative to Google Fonts. While Bunny Fonts claims to be privacy-friendly and GDPR-compliant, it still creates external dependencies and requires trusting a third party with your visitors' data. Even privacy-focused CDNs can potentially track usage patterns and collect metadata about your site and visitors."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:84
msgid "Even privacy-focused font CDNs create external dependencies that slow your site and require trusting third parties. For true privacy, use self-hosted fonts or system fonts. Block Bunny Fonts to eliminate all external font dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:89
msgid "Block CDNJS Font Libraries"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:90
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:93
msgid "Block font libraries served from cdnjs.cloudflare.com."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:91
msgid "Blocks font libraries served from cdnjs.cloudflare.com, including Font Awesome, Open Sans, and other popular web fonts. CDNJS is Cloudflare's free open source CDN that hosts thousands of libraries. While convenient, loading fonts from CDNJS allows Cloudflare to see your visitors' IP addresses and browsing patterns. Cloudflare processes massive amounts of internet traffic and this creates potential privacy concerns."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:92
msgid "CDNJS gives Cloudflare visibility into your visitors' behavior and browsing patterns. While Cloudflare claims to respect privacy, they still collect extensive data. Block CDNJS fonts to prevent this third-party tracking and improve page load speed."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:97
msgid "Remove from HTML Output"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:98
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:101
msgid "Scan and remove external font references from HTML."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:99
msgid "Scans the final HTML output before it's sent to browsers and removes any remaining external font references that weren't caught by the WordPress hooks. This catches font links added by themes that bypass WordPress' enqueue system, hardcoded links in templates, and fonts injected by page builders or other plugins. It also removes DNS prefetch and preconnect hints that can leak information to font CDNs."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:100
msgid "Some themes and plugins bypass WordPress standards and add font links directly to HTML, evading normal blocking methods. Enable HTML output scanning to catch these sneaky font references and ensure complete external font blocking across your entire site."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:105
msgid "Advanced Settings"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:106
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:109
msgid "Configure whitelist, system fonts, and debug options."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:107
msgid "Fine-tune font blocking behavior with advanced options. Create a whitelist of specific external fonts you want to allow while blocking others. Configure custom system font fallbacks to replace blocked fonts with privacy-friendly alternatives. Enable admin-only blocking to block fonts in admin area while allowing them on frontend. Turn on debug logging to see exactly what fonts are being blocked in your browser console for troubleshooting."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:108
msgid "Advanced controls let you whitelist specific fonts you need while blocking everything else, replace blocked fonts with beautiful system fonts, and debug any issues. These options give you complete control over font blocking behavior without compromising your site's design."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:435
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:449
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:483
msgid "External Fonts Privacy"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:452
#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:486
msgid "Privacy"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:455
msgid "External font blocking is not enabled. Blocking external fonts improves privacy by preventing third-party tracking."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:493
#, php-format
msgid "External font blocking is active with %d protection layers enabled. Your site is not loading fonts from external CDN servers."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-external-fonts-disabler.php:537
msgid "Settings saved successfully."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:33
#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:235
#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:250
#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:271
msgid "Hotlink Protection"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:34
msgid "Stop other sites from stealing your bandwidth - protect your images and files."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:35
msgid "Prevent bandwidth theft by blocking other websites from directly linking to your images, videos, and media files. Hotlinking occurs when other sites embed your media files directly in their pages, using your server resources and bandwidth without permission. This feature automatically configures server-level protection using .htaccess rules for Apache/LiteSpeed servers, provides configuration guidance for Nginx servers, and includes recommendations for CDN-level protection for maximum effectiveness."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:36
msgid "Hotlinking is when other websites steal your bandwidth by directly linking to your images and files. Every time someone views their site, your server pays the cost. This can significantly increase your hosting bills and slow down your site. Enable this to automatically block unauthorized embedding and protect your server resources."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:37
msgid "Prevent bandwidth theft with automatic hotlink blocking."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:63
msgid "Apache .htaccess Protection"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:64
msgid "Automatic server-level hotlink blocking for Apache."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:65
msgid "Automatically configures Apache/LiteSpeed servers with .htaccess rules that check the HTTP referer header and block requests from unauthorized domains. Rules are written to your uploads directory .htaccess file and are automatically updated when you enable or disable the feature. Works seamlessly with Apache, LiteSpeed, and compatible web servers."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:66
msgid "If your server runs Apache or LiteSpeed, this will automatically configure hotlink protection at the server level. No manual configuration needed - just enable and the protection activates immediately. Most shared hosting uses Apache."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:67
msgid "Auto-configure Apache/LiteSpeed .htaccess rules."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:71
msgid "Protect Image Files"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:72
msgid "Block hotlinking of JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP, and SVG images."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:73
msgid "Protects common image formats including JPEG, PNG, GIF, WebP, and SVG files from being hotlinked. Images are the most commonly stolen resource since they're easy to embed and can consume significant bandwidth. This protection ensures your images only display on your site and authorized domains, preventing bandwidth theft and unauthorized use."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:74
msgid "Images are the #1 target for hotlinking because they're easy to embed and use a lot of bandwidth. Protect your JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP, and SVG files to stop other sites from embedding them without permission."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:75
msgid "Protect JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP, SVG images."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:79
msgid "Protect Media Files"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:80
msgid "Block hotlinking of video and audio files."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:81
msgid "Protects video files (MP4, WebM, OGG) and audio files (MP3, WAV, OGG) from being hotlinked. Media files are especially costly to hotlink since they're large and consume significant bandwidth with each play. Blocking unauthorized embedding of your media files can dramatically reduce bandwidth usage and hosting costs if you host videos or audio files."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:82
msgid "Video and audio files are huge bandwidth hogs. If someone hotlinks your videos, your hosting bill can skyrocket. Enable this if you host any media files to prevent other sites from embedding them and using your bandwidth."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:83
msgid "Protect MP4, MP3, and other media files."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:256
msgid "Hotlink protection is not enabled. Other websites can embed your images and media files directly, using your bandwidth without permission and potentially increasing your hosting costs."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %d: number of protected file types
#: features/class-wps-feature-hotlink-protection.php:281
#, php-format
msgid "Hotlink protection is active with %d file type categories protected, preventing unauthorized embedding of your media files and reducing bandwidth theft."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:33
msgid "Iframe Busting (Clickjacking Protection)"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:34
msgid "Stop hackers from hiding your site in a malicious frame to trick your visitors."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:35
msgid "Protect your website from clickjacking attacks where malicious actors try to trick your visitors by loading your site inside an invisible iframe. This feature deploys multiple layers of defense including modern Content-Security-Policy headers, legacy X-Frame-Options headers for older browsers, and JavaScript frame-busting code as a final fallback. You can configure whether to completely block all framing, allow same-origin framing only, or whitelist specific trusted domains."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:36
msgid "Clickjacking is when hackers load your site in an invisible frame over a fake page to trick visitors into clicking things they didn't intend to. This can lead to stolen logins, unwanted actions, or data breaches. Enable this feature to block all framing attempts with industry-standard security headers and fallback protection for older browsers."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:37
msgid "Prevent clickjacking attacks with multi-layer frame protection."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:58
msgid "Content-Security-Policy Header"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:59
msgid "Modern browser frame-ancestors directive protection."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:60
msgid "Adds the Content-Security-Policy frame-ancestors directive, the modern standard for controlling who can embed your site in frames. This is supported by all current browsers and provides the most flexible and powerful protection. The CSP header can block all framing, allow same-origin only, or permit specific trusted domains through a whitelist."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:61
msgid "CSP headers are the modern way browsers block clickjacking. All current browsers support this, making it the strongest defense against framing attacks. This should always be enabled for maximum protection."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:62
msgid "Add CSP frame-ancestors header (recommended)."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:66
msgid "X-Frame-Options Header"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:67
msgid "Legacy browser clickjacking protection header."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:68
msgid "Adds the X-Frame-Options header for older browser compatibility. While superseded by CSP frame-ancestors in modern browsers, this header provides essential protection for visitors using older browsers like Internet Explorer 11 or older versions of Safari. Supports DENY (block all framing) and SAMEORIGIN (allow same-domain framing) modes."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:69
msgid "Old browsers don't understand modern CSP headers. The X-Frame-Options header ensures visitors with older browsers are still protected. Keep this enabled unless you're certain all visitors use current browsers."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:70
msgid "Add X-Frame-Options header for old browsers."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:74
msgid "JavaScript Frame-Buster"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:75
msgid "JavaScript fallback frame-breaking code."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:76
msgid "Injects JavaScript code that detects if your site is loaded in a frame and breaks out to the top window. This is a fallback protection layer for extremely old browsers that don't support security headers, or for situations where headers are stripped by proxies. The script is lightweight and loads before any other page content for maximum effectiveness."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:77
msgid "Some very old browsers or unusual network configurations might not respect security headers. JavaScript frame-busting provides a last line of defense by detecting and breaking out of frames directly in the browser. Adds minimal overhead."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:78
msgid "Add JavaScript frame-breaking code (fallback)."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:219
#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:234
#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:259
#: includes/features/class-wps-feature-http-ssl-audit.php:148
msgid "Clickjacking Protection"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:240
msgid "Clickjacking protection is not enabled. Your site could be vulnerable to framing attacks where malicious actors embed your site in invisible iframes to trick visitors."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %d: number of protection layers
#: features/class-wps-feature-iframe-busting.php:269
#, php-format
msgid "Clickjacking protection is active with %d protection layers enabled, preventing your site from being embedded in malicious iframes."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-skiplinks.php:30
msgid "Add Skip Navigation Links"
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-skiplinks.php:31
msgid "Help keyboard users navigate faster - add hidden skip links to main content."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-skiplinks.php:32
msgid "Improve website accessibility by automatically injecting skip navigation links that help keyboard users bypass repetitive navigation and jump directly to important page sections. Skip links are invisible until focused with the Tab key, providing a critical accessibility feature for users who navigate via keyboard. The feature intelligently detects common theme patterns and injects links to content, navigation, and footer areas with customizable styling."
msgstr ""

#: features/class-wps-feature-skiplinks.php:33
msgid "Keyboard users must tab through every navigation link to reach your content. Skip links let them jump directly to what they need. Enable this to meet WCAG 2.1 Level A accessibility requirements and provide a better experience for keyboard and screen reader users."
msgstr ""

