#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:168
msgid "Plugin Overview"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:171
msgid "Welcome to WPShadow"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:172
msgid "WPShadow is a comprehensive WPShadow and diagnostics plugin that works perfectly as a standalone core or optionally extends with specialized modules (Image Hub, Media Hub, Vault Storage, and more)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:175
msgid "Core Features"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:176
msgid "The core plugin includes health diagnostics, emergency support, backup verification, site documentation, activity logging, guided walkthroughs, and update simulation capabilities."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:179
msgid "Module Ecosystem"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:180
msgid "Extend functionality with optional modules for media optimization, vault storage, and specialized format support. Modules are completely optional - the core plugin provides full support functionality on its own."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:185
#: includes/views/dashboard-renderer.php:2171
#: includes/views/help.php:27
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:188
msgid "1. Dashboard Overview"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:189
msgid "Access the main dashboard from the Support menu. The dashboard provides an at-a-glance view of your site health, active modules, and quick actions."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:192
msgid "2. Configure Settings"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:193
msgid "Visit the Settings tab to configure module discovery, capability mapping, privacy options, and license settings. All settings include descriptions to guide you."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:196
msgid "3. Install Modules (Optional)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:197
msgid "Navigate to the Modules tab to browse and install optional modules. Each module extends the core plugin with specialized functionality. You can enable/disable modules at any time."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:200
msgid "4. Monitor Health"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:201
msgid "Use the built-in diagnostics to monitor site health, check for vulnerabilities, and validate backup integrity. Emergency support features are available when issues are detected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:206
msgid "Module Documentation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:207
msgid "Documentation for installed modules will appear here. Install modules from the Modules tab to extend functionality."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:210
msgid "Media Hub"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:211
msgid "Provides shared media optimization and processing infrastructure. Enables advanced image format support, optimization pipelines, and smart resizing capabilities."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:214
msgid "Vault Storage"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:215
msgid "Secure original file storage with encryption, versioning, and cloud offload. Protects originals while optimizing delivery copies for performance."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:218
msgid "Image Formats"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:219
msgid "Adds support for modern image formats including AVIF, WebP, HEIC, and various RAW camera formats. Automatic format conversion and optimization."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:224
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:227
msgid "Do I need to install modules?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:228
msgid "No. WPShadow works perfectly as a standalone core with full diagnostics, emergency recovery, backup verification, and documentation management. Install modules only if you need specialized features like media optimization or vault storage."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:231
msgid "How do I update the plugin?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:232
msgid "Updates are pulled automatically from GitHub releases. Configure auto-update settings in the Settings tab under License & Updates. You can choose which update types (major, minor, patch) to install automatically."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:235
msgid "Is multisite supported?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:236
msgid "Yes. Full multisite support with Network Governance. Network admins can manage settings globally while allowing site-level overrides where appropriate."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:239
msgid "How do I troubleshoot issues?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:240
msgid "Use the built-in diagnostics dashboard to identify issues. Enable diagnostic logging in Settings > Privacy & GDPR for detailed troubleshooting information. Emergency support features can isolate problematic plugins if needed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:243
msgid "Where is my data stored?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:244
msgid "All data is stored locally in your WordPress database. If you enable the Vault module, original files are stored in a secure wp-content/vault directory with optional cloud offload. No data is sent to external services without your explicit configuration."
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:247
msgid "Can I customize the dashboard?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/core/class-wps-help-content-api.php:248
msgid "Yes. Use Screen Options to adjust the number of columns and drag widgets to rearrange them. You can also collapse/expand widgets by clicking the toggle arrow. Your layout preferences are saved automatically."
msgstr ""

